commit.message:
Removed duplicate function

Removed duplicate `def __str__` function in `demos/cli/layer.py` file

[feat] force bytes type data in ProtocolTreeNode

ProtocolTreeNode will now raise AssertionError of passed data is not of
type bytes
Updated tests accordingly
Updated SyncResultIq and GetSyncIq
Deprecate str status text in SetStatusIq
Fixes #2796 TypeError: a bytes-like object is required, not 'str' in
line 74 yowsup/structs/protocoltreenode.py when sync contact

[fix] include djbtype as bytes

djbtype in SetKeysIq was encoded as str which broke due to recent
change in ProtocolTreeNode that required all node data to be bytes.

Fixes #2795 TypeError running echo demo

[fix] fix possible error in downloadable attrs str

in case file_sha256 or media_key is None
[feat] add onPresenceChange callback to cli demo

[fix] fix possible unique contraint violation

which might trigger during group message encrypt

Fixes #2755 sqlite3.DatabaseError: UNIQUE constraint failed

[fix] decode data as bytes instead of bytearray

Fixes decoding errors, for example when retrieving keys relevant to a
group.

Also updated enc protocolentity as node.data encoding is no longer
valid/necessary.

[fix] decode data as bytes/bytearray

Fixes #2759 a bytes-like object is required, not 'str' when trying to save picture

[log] update protocoltreenode __str__

- Pretty print
- Truncate long data
- Always use hex representation of data
[fix] omit streaming_sidecar from video attrs str
[fix] rm trailing slash in profile path construct

[fix] disable random prekey_id generation

To generate prekeys, previously a random number was first generated and
used as a starting point for a sequence of incrementing prekey_ids. This
had the flaw of potential non-unique ids being generated.

Additionally this behaviour makes it hard to debug some issues where
sent key were not accepted at server

Since this randomness is unnecessary, this commit changes the bahaviour to
generate prekey_ids starting from current max value of existing preykey_ids + 1.

Refs #2791 Cannot send messages - "Sent keys were not accepted" exception
Refs #2762 can't connect to whatsapp - Exception("Sent keys were not accepted")
